<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - PROSTAR&#8482; - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - TILT BRACKET</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>TILT BRACKET</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tilt Bracket - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release latches and lower the tilt-away bumper.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If equipped with fog lights, disconnect electrical connectors from fog lights.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two pins and locknuts from two bumper hinge bolts (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901101">Figure 2, Items 1, 2, and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide two bumper hinge bolts out of two chassis hinge brackets far enough to clear the
                    inside of the chassis hinge brackets (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901101">Figure 2, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clevis pin from each clevis and disconnect two support cables (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901102">Figure 3, Items 3, 4, and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the aid of an assistant, remove the tilt-away bumper from the chassis hinge
                    brackets and position bumper on a solid work surface (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901103">Figure 4, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901109" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901109.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Tilt Bracket Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TILT BRACKET MOUNT NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SUPPORT CABLE MOUNT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SUPPORT CABLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TILT BRACKET MOUNT BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HOOD CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. TILT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. MEGA BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolt and support cable from tilt bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove three bolts and nuts from tilt bracket, hood crossmember, and mega bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901110.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Tilt Bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TILT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HOOD CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MEGA BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tilt bracket from between the hood crossmember and mega bracket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tilt Bracket - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the tilt bracket between the hood crossmember and mega bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901110">Figure 12, Items 1, 2, and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install three bolts and nuts on tilt bracket, hood crossmember, and spring support
                    bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901109">Figure 11, Items 1 and 4</hotlnk>). Torque bolt to 70 to 85 lbf-ft (95 to
                    115 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install support cable on tilt bracket with one bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901109">Figure 11, Items 2, 3, and 6</hotlnk>). Torque bolt to 12 to 15 lbf-ft (16
                    to 20 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two bumper hinge bolts into the bumper hinge brackets making sure that the bolt
                    heads are on the outside of the hinge brackets and the ends of the bolts are not protruding through
                    the hinge brackets (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901103">Figure 4, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the aid of an assistant, install the tilt-away bumper on the chassis hinge brackets
                    (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901103">Figure 4, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slightly lift each side of the tilt-away bumper to slide the mount bolts completely
                    through the chassis hinge brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect two support cables to the tilt-away bumper with a clevis and clevis pin on each
                    side (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901102">Figure 3, Items 3, 4, and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two mount nuts on two bumper hinge bolts (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901101">Figure 2, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>). Torque bolts
                    to 12 to 15 lbf-ft (16 to 20 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two pins through holes in two hinge bracket bolts (
                    <hotlnk document="s09011_14.xml" xrefid="f0901101">Figure 2, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If equipped with fog lights, connect electrical connector to fog lights.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the tilt-away bumper and secure latches.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
